    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="593"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.248/222: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-05T21:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 5, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 5—8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>243. For the President. One of the items on the list submitted to the Harriman
                    Mission in September [1941] by the Soviet Naval authorities was a request for
                    PBY Navy planes. These planes could not be spared at that time. The Navy
                        Commissar<note n="9" xml:id="d593fn9">Adm. Nikolay Gerasimovich
                        Kuznetsov.</note> now informs me that he has again requested 60 PBY planes
                    for use in the Vladivostok and Murmansk–Archangel areas, and I am convinced that
                    if these <pb facs="0718" n="712" xml:id="pg_712"/> planes could be spared they
                    would be of great value in protecting convoys in those areas and thus prevent
                    sinkings of many cargo ships. It would be of great help in my work here if your
                    answer were delivered through me.<note n="10" xml:id="d593fn10">No reply to this
                        communication has been found in Department files.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
